values:
Has anyone ever wanted to burn everything they&#39;ve ever written?

I&#39;ve spent the last four days editing the heck out of everything I&#39;ve written for anything unscriptural, and taken almost half of it off the internet, including two novel length explicitly Christian&nbsp;fanfictions that could be taken to misrepresent how someone gets into heaven.

I know&nbsp;that&nbsp;worring so much about what I write is&nbsp;a kind of idolatory, and&nbsp;don&#39;t feel close to God at all compared to last week, but I can&#39;t be indifferent&nbsp;if I&#39;ve&nbsp;posted something&nbsp;against God. I&#39;d like to write much better stories than the ones I have before, but at the moment, I&nbsp;feel sick of the whole thing and unable to look away.&nbsp;How can I write about God, when misrepresenting Him is worse than not writing at all?&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;

I haven't posted about work for some time since there hasn't been anything overwhelmingly positive to report since presenting my work at the SCI symposium a few months ago, and no huge problems. The lack of a real deadline, particularly, has made it difficult to guage how well I am doing overall.

Last Friday, my supervisor found out that another research group are working on the same chemistry as us and about to publish. I had first a month, then another week to do what I've haven't managed to complete in the past year, though to an achievable rather than perfect standard.

Definately things to do...definately praying about it.&nbsp;

&nbsp;Gran went into hospital with a chest infection a few days ago, back home in Bristol. Mum and Dad are surprised by how well she seems now, but she's still at risk. I knew there would be a time in the future when she wasn't around, but&nbsp;before this i hadn't&nbsp;started anticipating. 

&nbsp;Otherwise, too much work,&nbsp;conference presentation&nbsp;next month (certain results really need to be in before then), My home church is soldiering on as well.&nbsp;The long&nbsp;fanfic with Chloe's backstory is being difficult; lets hope its worth it. 

&nbsp;Don't seem to make&nbsp;too many of these personal update posts. 

&nbsp; 

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
